Socotra is considered the jewel of biodiversity. 700 endemic species were found in this island through survey conducted by a team of UN biologists. 307 out of 825 plant species on socotra are endemic. The entire flora of socotra has been put in ICUN red list, 3 critically endangered and 27 endangered plants species recognized in 2003-4. Dragon blood tree (Dracaena cinniabari) is strage looking, umbrella shape which is only found in socotra and used as a dye and varnish. It's our duty to preserve them before its too late.
